He pulled his daily food costs as the “proof” that his waitress/hostess did not steal anything.  Accountants/bookkeepers like myself know that gratuities are calculated differently and do not go to offset his food costs but are distributed as income to the servers, boosting their pay from 2.13 to something closer to minimum wage.  But....I was supposed to believe that because he had a printed receipt showing the charges from the food/menu prices that his employee was honest and not a thief at all.  I’m disappointed I can never go back there and I encourage anyone who can not pay cash also STAY AWAY.  The will steal from you

At first, we did not know if Mike Cocina should be trusted seeing how we are in Kentucky, which is not known for their Mexican food, but we were pleasantly surprised.  First, the location is just outside of 4th Street Live, which is a great and fun area. Second, their prices aren't bad at all; especially for a downtown restaurant. One of the first things you notice is the large bar with a huge selection of wine, a nice selection of liquor and beer, and a small draft section. The restaurant also has a lot of space, which could be great for large groups.  We we're greeted as we walked through the door and immediately sat at our table. Our server came quickly and took our drink orders. Nicole ordered a sweet tea (like normal) and I ordered a strawberry daquiri (one of my favorites).  We we're also given free chips and two salsas. I don't think the salsa was anything special, but Nicole enjoyed it. One was pretty much just tomato sauce, but the other definitely had more flavor.  Nicole ordered their tacos al pastor and I ordered their carne asada steak. We started with their appetizer of queso with chorizo. The appetizer was very tasty.  Their carne asada was only okay, but their tacos al pastor was pretty dang good. Needless to say, we took all of our leftovers home with us. If you're looking for Mexican food, you should definitely check this place out.
